      "content": "The school's emphasis on \"inclusivity\" inherently prioritizes a specific social philosophy, which often means their version of acceptance is presented as the necessary standard for a modern educational environment. To truly balance these views, the school would need to adopt a highly nuanced approach, which is rarely achievable in practice. In reality, when a school mandates curriculum changes, their institutional authority dictates that their vision of inclusivity takes precedence over individual parental objections.",
